sentences: JS Clayden (born Jonathan Seth Clayden, 24 March 1971) is a British singer/songwriter.
He moved to several towns in the United Kingdom, settling in Nottingham, England for a number of years before emigrating to Los Angeles, California.
In 1989, Clayden, along with his brother and bassist/programmer Mark Clayden, formed the musical group Pitchshifter (then called "Pitch Shifter"), going on to found PSI Records in 2002.
